>How do I get a refund?</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease contact us to discuss this.','FAQs','','publish','closed','closed','','faqs','','','2018-02-12 13:45:59','2018-02-12 13:45:59','',0,'http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/?page_id=494',0,'page','',0),(495,1,'2018-02-12 13:45:59','2018-02-12 13:45:59','<strong>How many colours can I choose from?</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are 10 colours available.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I get a custom selection of cards?</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease contact us to arrange a custom order.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you post within the UK?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes, we use the Royal Mail 1st class delivery service.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you post to other countries?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes, however items can take up to 15 days to deliver depending on the the country you are located in. We also use the Royal Mail delivery service for international orders. If your country isn\'t available, please contact us for a postage quote.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do I mould squishy plastik into different shapes?</strong>\r\n\r\nSee the \'About\' page for instructions on how to do so.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do I get a refund?</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease contact us to discuss this.','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','494-revision-v1','','','2018-02-12 13:45:59','2018-02-12 13:45:59','',494,'http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/uncategorised/494-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(496,1,'2018-02-12 13:50:46','2018-02-12 13:50:46','You might be an artist who would like to introduce yourself and your work here or maybe you’re a business with a mission to describe.\n\n<strong>What is Squishy Plastik?</strong>\n\nSquishy Plastik is a non-toxic biodegradable product. Squishy Plastik is a low melting point thermoplastic which softens at 60 degrees Celsius.\n\n<strong>What can Squishy Plastik be used for?</strong>\n\nSquishy Plastik has 1000s of uses from home application to creative. For example:\n<ul>\n 	<li>DIY</li>\n 	<li>Fixing</li>\n 	<li>Prototyping</li>\n 	<li>Jewellery making</li>\n 	<li>Toys and games</li>\n 	<li>Moulds</li>\n 	<li>Science related projects</li>\n</ul>\nThe only limit is your imagination!\n\n&nbsp;','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','186-autosave-v1','','','2018-02-12 13:50:46','2018-02-12 13:50:46','',186,'http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/uncategorised/186-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(497,1,'2018-02-12 13:50:57','2018-02-12 13:50:57','','instructions selfix','','inherit','open','closed','','instructions-selfix','','','2018-02-12 13:50:57','2018-02-12 13:50:57','',186,'http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/instructions-selfix.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(498,1,'2018-02-12 13:51:28','2018-02-12 13:51:28','You might be an artist who would like to introduce yourself and your work here or maybe you’re a business with a mission to describe.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is Squishy Plastik?</strong>\r\n\r\nSquishy Plastik is a non-toxic biodegradable product. Squishy Plastik is a low melting point thermoplastic which softens at 60 degrees Celsius.\r\n\r\n<strong>What can Squishy Plastik be used for?</strong>\r\n\r\nSquishy Plastik has 1000s of uses from home application to creative. For example:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>DIY</li>\r\n 	<li>Fixing</li>\r\n 	<li>Prototyping</li>\r\n 	<li>Jewellery making</li>\r\n 	<li>Toys and games</li>\r\n 	<li>Moulds</li>\r\n 	<li>Science related projects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe only limit is your imagination!<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-497\" src=\"http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/instructions-selfix.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1140\" height=\"584\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','186-revision-v1','','','2018-02-12 13:51:28','2018-02-12 13:51:28','',186,'http://homepages.shu.ac.uk/~b6031184/selfix_technology/uncategorised/186-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(499,1,'2018-02-12 13:52:20','2018-02-12 13:52:20',' ','','','publish','closed','closed'